<br>
Maybe part of the problem is I'm not really lower-end myself anymore.  I lead regular planes raids, after all.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   So I'd definitely like to hear some opinions from players who are still chugging along in their 20s and 30s, and who expect to be there for a while.  What does concern you, in terms of message board activities, enforcement, and policies?<br>
<br>
I guess what I'm afriad of is just the general perception that the end game is all that matters.  And I don't want to see a message board top-heavy with rules that cater to the concerns of the end game.  I'd sooner see an enforcement of respect and good behaviour.  A &quot;you dish it you take it&quot; policy seems to lead to an escalating situation that can get way out of hand.<br>
<br>
So really, there aren't any issues solely particular to the lower-end game.  There are, however, issues particular to the higher-end game.  And then there are issues that do, or should, concern us all.  If the message board is going to be policed over ebay, SH-transfers, etc. then that's fine, but remember those matters are of meaning to only some of the population of FV.  But questions of respect, integrity, and responsibility to fellow players matter to everyone, from level 1 on up to level 60.  And that's where I'd like to see the focus of any message board moderation.<br>
<br>
Just my perspective.<br>
<br>
Valquiss<br>
<br>
P.S.  I do believe you are focused on your personal pet peeves, Apep, but that isn't meant to be a criticism.  It's human nature.  I would encourage you, however, to recruit a few new mods who are on totally different issues and who have completely different perspectives.  It would probably help a lot.<br>
<br>
P.P.S.  Ermok, you aren't even worth flaming properly anymore.  I just think it's a shame that you are so ineffectual you are reduced to trivializing the accomplishments and the work of everyone around you while doing nothing yourself.  And yes, I know you are level 60 with a swack of AA points, and you've pointed out in the past what an awful lot of work that was.  Congradulations.  Really.  I mean it.  Work hard at the game while the rest of us get on with life and relax in Norrath in our spare time.  It's good you've found your level and are comfortable with it. <p><img src=http://www.traveling.freehosting.net/valquisssig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaritzia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maritzia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Uptight Cleric</span><br>  Posts: 587<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/16/02 9:59:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1393.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Apep Speaks</span><hr size=1> Well, speaking as one of those perpetual 20-30 level characters, and one unlikely to *ever* see the high end game, I have to say that I don't actually have any concerns about this board.  I think Apep and the other mods have done a good job of policing the excrement that flied regularly, and my hats are off to them.<br>
<br>
I come here for a variety of reasons:  to keep up with what's happening on the rest of the server, to learn to play my class better (the higher end folks are a fount of information), to ask questions about general game mechanics, and just to plain enjoy myself and meet people.  I think the server is well suited for all those things the way it stands.<br>
<br>
